puzzle.help: 1. Fill some tiles with numbers. The numbers form a Nurikabe, that is a path interconnected horizontally or vertically and which can' t cover a 2x2 area. 2. All numbers in an area must be the same and all of them must be equal to the number of those numbers in the area. 3. All regions must have at least one number. 4. Two orthogonally adjacent tiles across areas must be different.
